<font color="#FF0000">THE FIRST TIME I MET MTF</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 13 19:35:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I've never forgotten the first time I met Ed;<br><br>
Ed was flying his helicopter around our TO, southwest of Da Nang. It was his first time out and wasn’t familiar with the terrain, when an electrical malfunction disabled all of his aircraft's electronic navigation and communications equipment. Due to the clouds and haze, Ed could not determine the helicopter's position and course to steer to the Da Nang airport. <br>
He saw a small Hill with US military personnel on it and flew toward it, circled, drew a hand-written sign, and held it in the helicopter's window. <br>
The sign read: &quot;WHERE AM I?&quot; in large letters. We quickly responded to the aircraft, drew a large sign, and held it up from our guns bunker.<br>
Their sign read &quot;YOU ARE IN A HELICOPTER.&quot; <br>
The pilot smiled, waved, looked at his map, determined the course to steer to the DaNang airport, and landed safely. After they were on the ground, his copilot asked Ed how the &quot;YOU ARE IN A HELICOPTER&quot; sign helped determine their position. Ed responded: &quot;I knew that it had to be the Marines on Hill 65 because, similar to their training, they gave me a true but completely useless answer.&quot; <br><br>

<p><code>--   (Anonymous) </code><p>


